<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3270] Deployment admin incorrectly takes snapshots of bundle data areas</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3270</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The deployment admin implementation relies on a SnapshotCommand to make snapshots of bundle data areas. However, dus to a mistake in the store() method, these snapshots don&apos;t work. The method incorrectly invokes storeRecursive(). We actually ran into this issue because we saw an update deployment fail (hanging in this method because it managed to create an infinity copy).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;storeRecursive(target, ... -&amp;gt; storeRecursive(source, ...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
